  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Rehabilitation Application**\n\nI\'m focusing on the core requirement: a rehabilitation scheduling application. My initial analysis pinpoints therapists and patients as the primary user groups. I\'m taking into account the need for both PC and mobile compatibility, and Japanese language support is also essential to consider.\n\n\n**Evaluating Database Solutions**\n\nI\'m now assessing database options. Firebase integration seems relevant, but I need to decide between Firestore and a relational database. My current thinking leans towards a relational database due to the application\'s constraints: time slots, patient/therapist matching with attributes, and scheduling rules. Constraints include no double-booking, avoiding NG combinations, allocating required orders, and therapist breaks. I\'m weighing these factors now.\n\n\n**Developing Optimization Approach**\n\nI\'m now diving into optimization. It looks like we\'ll need a smart scheduler, likely using a heuristic or a solver with techniques like simulated annealing or local search, implemented in TypeScript. I\'m focusing on two key constraints: ensuring at least a 40-minute gap between patient rehab sessions and minimizing the variance in slots assigned per therapist for load balancing. I\'m also planning the UI features: a dashboard for an overview, a schedule board for manual adjustment, and an order management section.\n\n\n**Defining Therapist Profiles**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing therapist management. I\'m focusing on their profiles: specialties (PT, OT, ST), available slots, breaks, and existing commitments. It\'s critical to accurately reflect this data for the auto-scheduler. I\'m also now thinking about implementing a randomized greedy heuristic or a constraint solver in TypeScript for the auto-scheduler, along with visual progress feedback.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will check the guidelines for Firebase Integration to understand how to correctly set up and configure the Firestore database for this schedule management application."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 315371124
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
