en the lowest soft constraint penalty, and lastly, the lowest therapist workload variance. The score function is now precisely defined: `Score = (Soft Violations * 100) + (Therapist Workload Variance * 500)`. This formula effectively balances soft constraints and workload variance minimization. I\'m verifying the workload variance calculation.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/utils/scheduler.ts` which implements the scheduling optimizer and real-time constraint validation. The algorithm uses a **multi-restart randomized constructive heuristic** coupled with **local search refinement** to find solutions that strictly satisfy all hard constraints (no overlaps, NG matches, mandatory therapist breaks, busy slots) while minimizing soft penalties (insufficient rehab spacing) and the target objective function (therapist workload variance). It also includes a validator to check for real-time constraint violations when users make manual adjustments."
