  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Building Core Components**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased with the scheduling foundation; it\'s elegant. My focus has shifted to constructing the essential components. I\'ve initiated work on the `/src/components/Dashboard.tsx`, `/src/components/ScheduleGrid.tsx`, `/src/components/TherapistList.tsx` and am already making progress.\n\n\n**Refining Dashboard Details**\n\nMy focus has shifted to the `/src/components/Dashboard.tsx` implementation. It needs summary stats in a card grid: assigned slots versus orders, violations (hard and soft), and a therapist burden score. Action buttons for auto-generation (optimizer launch!), data reset, JSON import/export are essential. I\'m also planning a custom SVG workload balancing chart and a constraint health panel.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/Dashboard.tsx` to serve as the control center of the application. It will display high-level KPI cards, a custom-designed reactive SVG chart showing the therapist workload balancing distribution with an average reference line, and detailed lists of hard/soft constraint health checks. It will also provide buttons to trigger the auto-scheduling solver, import/export schedule JSON files, and reset to defaults."
