  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Schedule Grid Function**\n\nI\'m focusing on defining the `/src/components/ScheduleGrid.tsx` component. My primary concern is that it accurately and clearly represents the schedule data. The component needs to support therapist-wise views (time slots vs. therapists). I am brainstorming ways to implement this view effectively.\n\n\n**Designing Schedule Views**\n\nI\'ve been working on defining two primary schedule views within the grid: Therapist-wise and Patient-wise. To make this practical, I\'m integrating a view selector tab, along with filter controls for therapist type and patient search. The grid itself will display time slots in the left column, with therapists or patients as column headers. Cells will display patient cards if assigned, or break blocks where applicable, with controls for editing and reassignment.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/ScheduleGrid.tsx`. It provides an interactive timeline schedule board that supports two main views: viewing by Therapist (columns representing therapists, rows representing time slots) and viewing by Patient (columns representing active patients, rows representing time slots). It features search filters, specialty tabs, responsive horizontal scrolling, visual indicators for breaks and busy slots, and click-to-assign / click-to-edit interactions allowing instant manual corrections that trigger immediate constraint checks."
