  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Natural Tones Design**\n\nI\'ve reviewed the codebase and now I\'m carefully analyzing the \"Natural Tones\" design specifications. I\'m starting with the HTML specs, specifically the body/main background color, which is `#F7F8F3`. My plan is to thoroughly implement this design theme.\n\n\n**Implementing Color Palette**\n\nI\'ve defined a core color palette with soft charcoal, slate deep green-charcoal, muted herbal sage green, muted gold/sand/wheat, and deep evergreen. I\'m exploring how to best implement these as CSS variables within `src/index.css`, considering Tailwind\'s `@theme` directive, Tailwind classes, and custom CSS for bulletproof styling. I\'m aiming for a clean and elegant design using both approaches.\n\n\n**Defining Core Styling Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating the new color palette, font definitions and checking theme settings. I\'ve imported Google Fonts and defined variables for fonts and colors: slate-50, slate-100, slate-200, slate-500, slate-600, slate-800. Next step, I\'m defining the basic theme settings in `src/index.css` by using the theme directive.\n\n\n**Mapping Tailwind Colors**\n\nI\'ve determined that mapping these colors directly to the Tailwind theme is incredibly elegant. This method seamlessly integrates the \"Natural Tones\" palette, which makes class names consistent and makes markup consistent too! I\'m now verifying the exact Tailwind color mappings, like `indigo-600` for primary buttons to `#6D8B74` and other components that can be customized to the theme.\n\n\n**Refining Tailwind Integration**\n\nI\'m now diving deeper into the specific Tailwind mappings and theming. It looks like `bg-slate-50` correctly translates to `#F7F8F3`, and `bg-indigo-600` maps to `#6D8B74`, just as planned. I\'m verifying the mapping of all primary, secondary, and tertiary colors with `hover` states, ensuring the color variables align for consistency. I\'m also writing a Tailwind `@theme` section within `src/index.css` to bring everything together.\n\n\n**Incorporating Color Values**\n\nI\'ve got the specific color values now, neatly organized as CSS custom properties. I\'m focusing on incorporating these new definitions, like `--color-slate-100` and others, to get a handle on the exact values. I\'m also reviewing the opacity values for each variant of the color definitions.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now update `/src/index.css` to import beautiful organic fonts (\"Outfit\" and \"Inter\") and configure the Tailwind theme using the exact Natural Tones palette, mapping the generic primary/slate colors to sage green, warm cream, earth gold, and slate charcoal."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 14
      nanos: 786269708
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
